Sentencas: We report electrical characteristics of a porous composite cathode for the solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) consisting of ZnO nanowires (ZnO-NW) and yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) particles.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of ZnO-nanowire/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite as a cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: This composite cathode significantly reduces concerns about chemical and mechanical compatibility with the YSZ electrolyte, which has remained one of the main challenges for practical utilization of the SOFC.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of ZnO-nanowire/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite as a cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The area-specific polarization resistivity of this composite electrode was comparable to, if not lower than, that of conventional cathodes.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of ZnO-nanowire/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite as a cathode for SOFCs

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that, with size and material optimization, the ZnO-NW/YSZ porous composite cathode can be a viable alternative to conventional cathodes for SOFCs.
Titulo: Electrochemical characteristics of ZnO-nanowire/yttria-stabilized zirconia composite as a cathode for SOFCs
